"Popel S.I., Kopnin S.I., Yu M.Y., Ma J.X., Huang F.","The effect of microscopic charged particulates in space weather",2011,"Journal of Physics D: Applied Physics","44","17", 174036,"","",,,10.1088/0022-3727/44/17/174036,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-79954569807&partnerID=40&md5=37f77eb4d451b853bd512a7f12419dc3","Institute for Dynamics of Geospheres RAS, Leninsky pr. 38, 119334 Moscow, Russian Federation; Institute for Fusion Theory and Simulation, Zhejiang University, Hangzhou 310027, China; Theoretical Physics i, Ruhr University, D-44780 Bochum, Germany; CAS Key Laboratory of Basic Plasma Physics, Department of Modern Physics, University of Science and Technology of China, Hefei, Anhui 230026, China; College of Science, China Agricultural University, Beijing 100083, China","Popel, S.I., Institute for Dynamics of Geospheres RAS, Leninsky pr. 38, 119334 Moscow, Russian Federation; Kopnin, S.I., Institute for Dynamics of Geospheres RAS, Leninsky pr. 38, 119334 Moscow, Russian Federation; Yu, M.Y., Institute for Fusion Theory and Simulation, Zhejiang University, Hangzhou 310027, China, Theoretical Physics i, Ruhr University, D-44780 Bochum, Germany; Ma, J.X., CAS Key Laboratory of Basic Plasma Physics, Department of Modern Physics, University of Science and Technology of China, Hefei, Anhui 230026, China; Huang, F., College of Science, China Agricultural University, Beijing 100083, China","Space weather is a relatively new and important field of research. It is relevant to diverse topics such as radio communication, space travel, diagnostics of ionospheric and space plasmas, detection of pollutants and re-entry objects, prediction of terrestrial weather and global warming. Recently it has been shown that nano- and micrometre-sized electrically charged particulates from interplanetary space and from the Earth's atmosphere can affect the local properties as well as the diagnostics of the interplanetary, magnetospheric, ionospheric and terrestrial complex plasmas. In this report the sources of the charged dust particulates and the effects of the latter on the near-Earth space weather are examined. © 2011 IOP Publishing Ltd.",,"Charged dust; Charged particulates; Complex plasma; Detection of pollutant; Interplanetary space; Local property; Near-earth spaces; Space plasmas; Space travel; Space weather; Terrestrial weather; Air pollution; Electric properties; Global warming; Magnetosphere; Pollution detection; Radio communication; Earth atmosphere",,,,,,"(2000) National Space Weather Program; Tobiska, W.K., Woods, T., Eparvier, F., Viereck, R., Floyd, L., Bouwer, D., Rottman, G., White, O.R., (2000) J. Atm. Sol. Terr. Phys., 62 (14), p. 1233; Daglis, I.A., (2001) Space Storms and Space Weather Hazards, , (NATO Science Series) (Dordrecht: Kluwer); Qahwaji, R., Colak, T., (2007) Sol. Phys., 241 (1), p. 195; Tobiska, W.K., (2008) Space Weather, 6 (6), p. 06001; Klotz, I., (2010) Space Weather, 8 (5), p. 05003; Verheest, F., (2000) Waves in Dusty Space Plasmas, , Dordrecht: Kluwer; Praburam, G., Goree, J., (1996) Phys. Plasmas, 3 (4), p. 1212; Amiranashvili Sh, G., Gusein-Zade, N.G., Tsytovich, V.N., (2004) Phys. Rev., 64 (1), p. 016407; Tsytovich, V.N., Vladimirov, S.V., Morfill, G.E., (2004) Phys. Rev., 70 (6), p. 066408; Tsytovich, V.N., Vladimirov, S.V., Morfill, G.E., Goree, J., (2001) Phys. Rev., 63 (5), p. 056609; Samsonov, D., Goree, J., (1999) Phys. Rev., 59 (1), p. 1047; Goree, J., Morfill, G.E., Tsytovich, V.N., Vladimirov, S.V., (1999) Phys. Rev., 59 (6), p. 7055; Akdim, M.R., Goedheer, W.J., (2001) Phys. Rev., 65 (1), p. 015401; Chu, J.H., Du, J.B., (1994) J. Phys. D: Appl. Phys., 27 (2), p. 296; Chu, J.H., (1994) Phys. Rev. Lett., 72 (25), p. 4009; Chan, C.L., Lai, Y.J., Woon, W.Y., Chu, H.Y., (2005) Plasma Phys. Control. Fusion, 47 (5 A), p. 273; Barkan, A., Merlino, R.L., D'Angelo, N., (1995) Phys. Plasmas, 2 (10), p. 3563; Morfill, G.E., Thomas, H.M., Konopka, U., Rothermel, H., Zuzic, M., Ivlev, A.